  Some classes are tuned to the races currently available (An ogre monk, for example, would probably be a little too insane on damage output/tankability compared to other monks), but certainly there's room for Ogre Magi, or gnome &amp; half-elf shadowknights, or barbarian bards (skalds), or halfling &amp; dark-elf rangers <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>   It's an issue that's been brought up in the past, and Verant has always said &quot;No no no, never, nada, no-way, negativo!&quot;, but they said that about NPCs that cast bind affinity as well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Maybe since the &quot;special ruleset&quot; servers are suffering some in the population department, some new rules which expanded a players options rather than limiting them would draw new people to the server.  <br><br>   It'd also be a change more likely to draw the role-playing oriented (versus implementing a server wide xp-bonus).<br><br>   Anyways, if you think it's a good idea, use /feedback to make a suggestion.  Maybe someone will actually listen to it (I know, I know... fat chance <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br><br>Syllestrae Silverblade<br>Warchanter of Rallos Zek<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usarhea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarhea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle> #2 cutie ranger</span><br>  Posts: 219<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/20/01 5:15:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=936.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top a