N A WEEKEND!... IN LOWER GUK!<br><br>   Okay, sorry for all the capital letters there, but that's just insane.  And that all happend *before* Luclin came out.  I frequently run through zones in which, on other servers, there's at least a little jostling for who has the rights to such-n-such a camp, but on our server you can see tumbleweeds blowing through.  I'm not saying I want jostling, but if I want to go hunt stuff in a really nice zone, I shouldn't have to go jogging 5 zones away, trying to recruit people who are likewise wandering around lost and groupless.<br><br>&quot;I think there are two huge barriers preventing the &quot;unwashed masses&quot; from flooding our server &quot;<br><br>Snob.  There's a ton of people who would fit in just great on the roleplay server, but don't see a ton of incentive to give up their established character on an older server.  Firiona-Vie provides a rules-set that helps create a more RP atmosphere, but all the rules limit playstyle, they don't expand it.  There is currently nothing you CAN do on FV that you CAN'T do on another server, except trade formerly no-drop items.<br><br>&quot;Of course, one method of mitigating this is to recruit other players. Talk about how much you enjoy FV over other servers, for example. Sure, that won't draw in a huge throng of people, but do we really want that and all that comes with it?&quot;<br><br>If I were to waste my days, travelling from server to server, spamming the OOC channels with advertisements for Firiona Vie, and perhaps track down the URLs of all the other server boards, and spam up some FV advertisements there as well, I'm fairly confident that at most I'd attract about 0 players <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    If I limited my advertising to former guilds, etc, I'd probably have more success, but seeing as I've already done that, that doesn't work for me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>Sorry for being so ranty, but the tone of your post seems to be that you don't like players from other servers, and don't want them here, and hence it's a bad idea. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Syllestrae Silverblade<br>Warchanter of Rallos Zek<br><br>Edit: removed a joke <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uevangelinanife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evangelina Nife</A> at: 12/20/01 6:21:45 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uitchibumbashalots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ItchibumBashalots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/20/01 6:49:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=936.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Would expanding race/class availability help server pop?</span><hr size=1> Awsome Song Hungra!!!<br><br>Syll sorry but I like the server with a low population.  Some people are frustrated because they are dashing ahead in levels and finding things...well...a bit lonely.  In a month or two the higher level zones will be filled with all the upstarts that are on our coat tails.<br><br>Scratchy and I got around this by picking Characters that truely compliment one another.  SK and Shami.  Both heal.  Both have pets.  One can buff the hell out of ya.  They both have invis.  SK can ITU.  We have SoW.  I can summon corpses eventually