ur group.  One of my favorite camps in L guk is the live side crawl to the king room.  Old old timers will recall that this used to be a &quot;raid&quot; style camp, where 20-30 people would set up for the final battle.  Of course in those days a Ykesha was the very height of uber...<br><br>A single group with a 51+ shaman at least a little crowd control (rooters or bard is enough) and about any other mix of classes can make the crawl from Live side entrance through the maze of minotaur passages, you meet a number of named mino's and frogs on the way, The Patriarch, The evil Eye, Froglok Noble, Herbalist, Tactician, and of course the King Himself.  The funnest part was always the insertion. Timing was critical as the dungeon was spawning behind you and you had to move fast or be swarmed... Drums in the deep best describes the feeling of this sort of crawl...<br><br>Good places for this are also found in most Kunark dungeons, Kaesora, Mines of Nurga, to name a couple.  A single well prepared (not necessarily balanced) group can crawl these places, never fighting the same battle twice and can be well rewarded in RP possibilities, loot, and cameraderie.  <br><br>One of my best EQ memories of this sort was a crawl in the mines of Nurga with a Cleric, 3 rangers, a monk, and and enchanter.  Nurga like many Kunark dungeons is one way, and without gate that means you have to crawl all the way through to get out if you arent a caster and don't have a Druid or wizard along.  We fell into traps, we were swarmed, at one point we had to do a naked crawl to where our corpses were pulled to the bottom of a ledge.  I managed to get a friendly mage in the Frontier mountains to summon 6 no rent magic swords... Even naked (well there isnt a lot of differencein ac than when dressed) 3 rangers can cuisinart quite effectively and we managed to pull off the corpse run and continue.<br><br>Where am I going with this?  EQ is flawed in that the most efficient way to play it is to set